---
title: Installing Spring Cloud Services for Pivotal Cloud Foundry
---

1. Spring Cloud Services requires [MySQL for Pivotal Cloud Foundry](https://network.pivotal.io/products/p-mysql) and [RabbitMQ for Pivotal Cloud Foundry](https://network.pivotal.io/products/pivotal-rabbitmq-service). If they are not installed, you can follow the same installation instructions below to install all products at the same time.

1. Download Spring Cloud Services for Pivotal Cloud Foundry from [Pivotal Network](https://network.pivotal.io/).

1. On the left sidebar, click Import Product to upload p-spring-cloud-services-&lt;version&gt;.pivotal
   
    <%= image_tag("pre-upload.png") %>

1. Hover over Spring Cloud Services in the Available Products list and click the Add button.

    <%= image_tag("pre-add.png") %>

1. Start the installation process by clicking Apply Changes on the right sidebar.

    <%= image_tag("post-add.png") %>

1. Go get a coffee. The installation process may take 20-30 minutes.

    <%= image_tag("applying-changes.png") %>

    When the installation process is complete you'll see the dialog below.

    <%= image_tag("changes-applied.png") %>

1. Congratulations! You have successfully installed Spring Cloud Services for Pivotal Cloud Foundry

    <%= image_tag("post-install.png") %>
    